text: The Hungarian alphabet () is the Latin alphabet used for writing the Hungarian language. The alphabet is based on the Latin alphabet, there are added variations of letters. The alphabet have 26 letters of the ISO basic Latin alphabet, and 5 letters with an acute accent, 2 letters with an umlaut, 2 letters with a double acute accent, 8 letters made up of two characters, and 1 letter made up of three characters. These characters are considered their own letters. Category:Hungary Category:Latin alphabet
title: Hungarian alphabet
